President Muhammadu Buhari has reappointed Dr. Garba Abari as the Director-General of the National Orientation Agency (NOA). The minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, announced the reappointment in a statement issued in Abuja yesterday. The appointment, which took effect from 25 May, 2021, is for a final term of five years. Abari was first appointed to the position in 2016. 